October 31, 2016

Correcting for Ground Skew on the November PF Topic By Liya Khan

On balance, the benefits of the Internet of Things outweigh the harms of decreased personal privacy.

The November topic presents an interesting comparative debate for this month. Debaters may not be used to the wording of this topic-where the Affirmative is allowed to weigh any benefit in the round while the Negative seems to just be restricted to defending the very narrow ground of harms to personal privacy.
